{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix VCD dump format mismatch in tracing system\n\n### Summary\nThe `vcd_dump()` function in the tracing system was failing to parse log entries due to a format mismatch between the textlog output and the expected input format. This caused VCD trace generation to fail with \"bad vcd_dump line\" errors.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/to_vcd.c`: \n  - Modified format string in logger setup from `\"%c [%s] %s\"` to `\"%c %s %s\"` to remove brackets around values\n  - Updated `sscanf` format from `%s` to `%255s` for variable name parsing to prevent buffer overflow\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running the VCD tracer with `-vcd` option, the system would crash with:\n```\nbad vcd_dump line '12:34:56.123456789: b [1] variable_name'\n```\n\nThis occurred because the textlog was producing entries with brackets around values (`[1]`) but `vcd_dump()` expected values without brackets (`1`). The format string mismatch caused `sscanf` to fail parsing, triggering the error exit path.\n\nAfter the fix, VCD traces are generated correctly without crashes.\n"
}